ATACseq Analysis Report

ATACseeker

October 04, 2015

ATACseeker Workflow

The raw reads are aligned to the hg19 assembly using bwa. Quality flags are made and duplicate reads are removed using samblaster. The produced bam files are then piped through csaw for a two-sample comparison.

QC metrics for the aligned reads are computed. Fragment size and window length to be used are estimated. Thereafter, the libraries are normalised and filtering of windows is done to retain high abundance windows. Finally, differential accessibility testing is done and corrrections for multiple testing is performed.

The design matrix used for the two-sample comparison is provided below.

Differential Accessibility Testing

Lets see how the samples are clustered:

y <- asDGEList(data, norm.factors=Norm.factors)
y <- estimateDisp(y, design)
fit <- glmQLFit(y, design, robust=TRUE)
results <- glmQLFTest(fit)
kable(topTags(results))
